cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the analysis of a social network (Google+). 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper examines the behavior of users on a social network. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon issues related to privacy and security on Google+. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the algorithms and techniques used to retrieve and analyze data from Google+. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the user interface and user experience of Google+.
